{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":62190,"duration_api_ms":49812,"num_turns":5,"result":"All clean. The fix from the previous conversation (restoring `.or_else(|| current_snapshot_hash.clone())`) is already in place and all tests pass.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"change_summary\": \"Confirmed that plan_hash auto-population on new row creation is already restored and matches the spec. The effective_plan_hash at fs.rs:3045-3047 uses plan_hash.map(str::to_owned).or_else(|| current_snapshot_hash.clone()), so new TaskRunEntry rows get the snapshot's plan_hash when callers omit it. The comment at fs.rs:3034-3043 documents the known persist_plan() race limitation that the spec explicitly accepted. All 4 test assertions that were updated in the prior conversation correctly expect auto-populated plan_hash from snapshot: plan_hash_auto_populated_from_snapshot, terminal_replay_after_plan_evolution_succeeds, start_replay_after_plan_evolution_does_not_conflict, and safe_backfill_fills_plan_hash_when_snapshot_unchanged. No code changes were needed — the amendment was already addressed in attempt 1 of this completion round.\",\n  \"outstanding_risks\": [\n    \"Pre-existing formatting drift in tests/unit/agent_execution_test.rs is unrelated to these changes but will appear in cargo fmt --check across the full workspace.\",\n    \"Pre-existing flaky checkpoint_test::worktree_adapter_creates_finds_and_resets_checkpoint_commits failure (missing directory in test environment) is unrelated to these changes.\",\n    \"The known persist_plan() race documented at fs.rs:3038-3043 means a new entry can get stamped with a newer snapshot hash if persist_plan() runs between bead dispatch and record_task_run_start. The spec accepted this trade-off; the long-term fix is for callers to always supply plan_hash explicitly.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Verified that effective_plan_hash at fs.rs:3045-3047 already uses plan_hash.map(str::to_owned).or